=head1 Padre 0.34 Released
=timestamp 1240924550
=tags Perl, Perl 5, Padre, IDE

I was a bit too busy with the <a href="http://www.perlworkshop.no/">Nordic Perl Workshop</a>
and the Perl 6 hackathon after that so this release got a bit delayed but 
I am happy to announce now that v0.34 of <a href="http://padre.perlide.org/">Padre, the Perl IDE</a>
has been released.

The full list of changes can be found <a href="http://svn.perlide.org/padre/trunk/Padre/Changes">here</a>.

Some of the highlights are
<ul>
<li>Support for plugin l10n in place.</li>
<li>Added Preferences->Run Parameters panel instead of Perl->Run Parameters menu option.</li>
<li>Stop refreshing the menus on every keystroke. Instead when the menu is being accessed.</li>
<li>Sessions support.</li>
<li>Enable tool-tips on the toolbar on Windows as well.</li>
<li>Plugin manager correctly localized at startup.</li>
<li>Plugin manager displaying full plugin names.</li>
<li>Double-clicking on an error now selects the line.</li>
</ul>

Please report any test failure via the padre-dev mailing list or
via our <a href="http://padre.perlide.org/">bug tracker</a>.

enjoy

